<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="487" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2314a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-09T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 9,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>10. Department is informed that about 200 armed Honduranean political
                            refugees are making depredations on Honduran border districts and have
                            robbed towns of Paraiso, San Antonio de Flores and Duyure. Make urgent
                            representations to Nicaraguan Government in order that it may stop the
                            activities of this band and reconcentrate the leaders.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>